Author:  YATE
Vol / Page:  108
Edition:
Quote:  When the stones are heated to redness, they are taken out of the oven, and the place cleaned from any remains of burning wood; a part of the hot stones are then placed in the oven again; and a wreath of damped leaves is laid round the outside, to prevent the earth from falling in, or the food from rolling to the side.
